import React from 'react'; import './Menu.sass' import PathfindingVisualizer from './PathfindingVisualizer/PathfindingVisualizer.jsx'; import backtracking from './' function visualizeAlgorithm(props,value) { switch(value) { case 1: document.getElementById('button').innerHTML = "Visualize Backtracking" props.selectedAlg = 1 console.log(props.selectedAlg) break case 2: document.getElementById('button').innerHTML = "Visualize Simulated Annealing" props.selectedAlg = 2 console.log(props.selectedAlg) break default: console.log("You selected an algorithm!") break } } export default function Menu(props) { return (
  1. About
  2. Algorithm
    1. console.log(props)}>Backtracking
    2. visualizeAlgorithm(props,2)}>Simulated Annealing
    3. Huge Dicks
  3. Kabobs
    1. Shishkabobs
    2. BBQ kabobs
    3. Summer kabobs
  4. Contact
) }
